## Testing with Fakes

Most unit tests should use fakes instead of making network requests to Google
services.

{{#Services}}
- Code that uses `{{Name}}` can be tested by injecting the
  fake `Fake{{Name}}`.
{{/Services}}
{{#Codec.ExampleMethodName}}

Import the fakes from the testing library:

```dart
import 'package:{{Codec.PackageName}}/testing.dart';
```

### Option A: Using Constructor Closures (Recommended)
You can inject behavior by passing optional function callbacks to the fake's
constructor. Methods that are not provided will throw an `UnsupportedError`.

```dart
import 'package:{{Codec.PackageName}}/{{Codec.MainFileNameWithExtension}}';
import 'package:{{Codec.PackageName}}/testing.dart';

final fake = Fake{{Codec.ExampleServiceName}}(
  {{Codec.ExampleMethodName}}: (request) async {
    // Assert request contents here if needed.
    {{#Codec.ExampleMethodReturnsValue}}
    return {{Codec.ExampleMethodResponseType}}();
    {{/Codec.ExampleMethodReturnsValue}}
  },
);
```

### Option B: Subclassing the Fake
For more complex test setups or shared states, you can subclass the fake and
override its methods. Methods that are not overridden will throw an
`UnsupportedError`.

```dart
import 'package:{{Codec.PackageName}}/{{Codec.MainFileNameWithExtension}}';
import 'package:{{Codec.PackageName}}/testing.dart';

final class MyFake{{Codec.ExampleServiceName}} extends Fake{{Codec.ExampleServiceName}} {
  @override
  Future<{{Codec.ExampleMethodResponseType}}> {{Codec.ExampleMethodName}}(
    {{Codec.ExampleMethodRequestType}} request,
  ) async {
    // Assert request contents here if needed.
    {{#Codec.ExampleMethodReturnsValue}}
    return {{Codec.ExampleMethodResponseType}}();
    {{/Codec.ExampleMethodReturnsValue}}
  }
}
```

## A Simple Test

```dart
import 'package:{{Codec.PackageName}}/{{Codec.MainFileNameWithExtension}}';
import 'package:{{Codec.PackageName}}/testing.dart';
import 'package:test/test.dart';

Future<void> functionUnderTest({{Codec.ExampleServiceName}} service) async {
  // Application logic here.
  await service.{{Codec.ExampleMethodName}}({{Codec.ExampleMethodRequestType}}());
  // More application logic here.
}

void main() {
  test('test', () async {
    final fake = Fake{{Codec.ExampleServiceName}}(
      {{Codec.ExampleMethodName}}: (request) async {
          // Assert request contents here.
          {{#Codec.ExampleMethodReturnsValue}}
          return {{Codec.ExampleMethodResponseType}}();
          {{/Codec.ExampleMethodReturnsValue}}
      },
    );
    // Instead of verifying that `functionUnderTest`, you should verify the
    // relevant properties of the result.
    await expectLater(functionUnderTest(fake), completes);
  });
}
```
